[head=2]Relief of Duty[/head][/color]

For this form to be valid, the head of the department that the employee worked in must release the employee from their current responsibilities to their department.

[bold]Department head[/bold], by stamping this form, you formally and officially release the employee from their obligations and responsibilities to your department. Only stamp this form if the employee is present and verbally confirms that they were the one to fill the form, and they wish to depart from your department.

[bold]Priority Acceptance[/bold]
After the completion of this form, the employee will be removed from their position, and become a passenger of the station. As a passenger, the employee has priority acceptance back into the department they originally departed from. This priority acceptance means that the Head of Personnel can approve a Job Application for the individual to their department without further needing approval from either the Head of the Department, or from the Captain.

[color=RoyalBlue]──────────────────────────────────────[/color]

[color=Gray]This form is only valid when stamped by the Head of Personnel as well as either the head of the department of employment or the Captain.[/color]
